I'm trying to decide what happens when we die. I find it almost impossible to believe that after about 70 years of intelligent life that it just ends for eternity, and that we are not aware of it. But I dont really believe in god - or do I? I dont believe a word written in the bible, but I cant really grasp the fact that we are here by accident or natural evolution. You people reading this accross the world thanks to the internet is not an accident, its intelligence, quite advanced too. Man has created electricity, ability to fly and explore space and more. Yet at around 70 years of age we die and all we have individually learned and experienced is lost. I dont think so. <br>
And what about ghosts. I am uncertain about them too. But stories about poltergeists throwing things and &quot;losts souls&quot; contacting us (for help?) are far too common to dismiss so how can they be explained. Do our souls die with our body, and if not then how can our souls exist without our bodies. I really need an answer on this before I die. Its more important to me than finding aliens or anything else.<br>
Driving me mad now!<br>
<br>
Matt  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/bunexplainedmysteries.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ghostdreamer>Ghost Dreamer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(11/25/02 2:38:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/funexplainedmysteriesfrm38.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=278.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: When we die?</span><hr size=1> Dear water dude,<br>
<br>
